dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_1812  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 28/6/2017 Pim\n- ACTN2 is localized in membrane and cytosolic synape preparations (Fig.2).\n- ACTN2 is localized to exc. synapses as shown by co-localization with Glur1\n- ACTN2 is mainly located at PSD (membrane and cytoplasmic part) and on microfilaments (a.k.a actin) (Fig.6).\n- ACTN2 is colocalizing at the inner face of the PSD membrane with the NR1 subunit (Fig.7).. Experimental description: M&M and results section\nImmunoblots of rat brain membranes\nMale Sprague Dawley rats were used for EM\nCrude synaptosomal membrane fraction from rat cortex" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1812" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

